Besides the quantitative variations in the main components, small variations were found in most of the EO compounds in each species; qualitative variations, such as the presence or absence of a certain compound in different seasons, were also observed (
 Table 1). In this study, a wide variation in the relative percentage of Î±-phellandrene was detected; this compound could be considered a major compound in spring (10%) and summer (11%). However, this result was not repeated in winter and autumn because the values were very low (0.4% and 0.3%, respectively; 
 Table 1).
